<a href="mailto:Minute@vastempire.net">My E-Mail</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Moderator <img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/goldstartr.gif align=middle><br><font color=#A0B0E0>&#60;Silent Redemption&#62;</font></span><br>  Posts: 1732<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/25/01 12:04:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Western Wastes</span><hr size=1> Uh, if you mean like as in a buff circle.  No way, you just continually buff just like any long raid such as fear or hate.  But other than that many of the dragons are similar to Vox/Naggy minus the Fear.  AEs are a bit stronger on some, some are very deadly.  Repop on all the dragons in WW are 2 hours except Klandicar (~3 days, Sleeper's Key dragon, now very nasty) and Sontalak (~24 hours, Sleeper's Key dragon, very nasty). <br>
<br>
Level 50 would be about minimum level.  But for a raid of 50+ with an average in the 54-55 range its very doable.  All descriptions below are for this type of raid of 24 people with an average in the 54/55 range.<br>
<br>
There are roaming dragons, nesting dragons, and guardian dragons.  <br>
<br>
Roaming dragons range from easy to very difficult.  Some are similiar to Naggy/Vox, others like Von have nasty AE's or proc's do 1200 dmg direct and then grav flux you for enough to fall for 10k if you don't have dmf up.<br>
<br>
Nesting dragons are the same.  From very easy to difficult.<br>
<br>
Guardian Dragons are those in the Temple of Veeshan scar and are some of the hardest ones in the zone.  Any of the Sapara's are alot more difficult than the rest. <br>
<br>
But you can easily spend hours in WW killing dragon after dragon and then kill them again after they repop.<br>
<br>
I HIGHLY recommend that everyone has at least 1 instant click buff item.  Either Jboots/Shaman Epic boots or a Shrunken Goblinskull Earring  or both.  By having that buff in your first buff slot it will generally get dispelled and you can click it to replace the buff. Stick a few junk buffs from slots 2-4 in case it skips the first buff. By doing this you will lose very few buffs.  If you have no instant click you will lose ALL your buffs EVERY fight.  That isn't really acceptable.  You will quickly be going buffless as the shaman and clerics will get really tired of buffing you after every fight all day long.  Go buy or camp jboots and goblin skull earring.  Tboots will NOT be acceptable.<br>
<br>
Resists are a big part too.  Minimum 100 FR/CR both at the same time UNbuffed.  Almost all dragons there have either FR or CR AE's.  Some have poison or disease but they can be avoided.  Few actually will fear.<br>
<br>
Here is a small list of the dragons, level, ae's, and talismans they drop. <br>
<br>
Amcilla  -  Level: 55  Casts: AE Cold and Dispell,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Atpaev  -  Level: 51  Casts: AE Cold and Dispell,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Cargalia  -  Level: ?  Casts: AE Cold and Dispell, Gravity Flux Proc,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Crial  -  Level: 57  Casts: AE Fire and Dispell,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Derasinal  -  Level: 58  Casts: AE Fire, Dispell and Disease,   Drops a +6 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Escorpa of the Ring  -  Level: ?  Casts: ?,   Drops a +5 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Gafala  -  Level: 53  Casts: AE Fire and Dispell,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Gangel  -  Level: ?  Casts: ?,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Harla Dar  -  Level: 63  Casts: AE Fear and Dispell,   Drops a +6 to stats/resists talisman<br>
