Karkona   -  Level: 57  Casts: AE Cold and Dispell,   Drops a +6 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Klandicar  -  Level: 63+  Casts: ?,   Drops a +7 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Mazi  -  Level: 54  Casts: AE Fire and Dispell,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Nyga  -  Level: ?  Casts: ?,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Pantrilla  -  Level: &lt;54  Casts: AE Cold and Dispell,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Vitaela  -  Level: 53  Casts: AE Cold and Dispell,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Vraptin  -  Level: ?  Casts: ?,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Yal  -  Level: 55  Casts: AE Fire and Dispel,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Yeldema  -  Level: 52  Casts: None,   Drops a +4 to stats/resists talisman<br>
Zil Sapara  -  Level: ?  Casts: ?,   Drops a +6 to stats/resists talisman<br>
<br>
<br>
 A &quot;+4 talisman&quot; as we call it is 5 AC 4 to all stats and resists  10 hp/mana  all/all  no drop.  There are +4, +5, +6, +7.  Each increase in + adds 1 to ac/stats/rests and 10 to hp/resists.  +7 talismans are sleepers key talismans and only come from Sontalak, Klandicar, Zlandicar, Yelinak, Lediniara the Keeper.  Lots of talismans will drop. Usually every other dragon has one.  I recommend making a master list of those wanting talismans and just doing a /random to find the winner each time.  Its so much easier than asking for names each time.  Just assign everyone numbers and go from there.  You can easily roll extra armor/spells that no one wants this way as well.<br>
<br>
Dragons will randomly drop Great Dragon Heads and Greater Dragon Heads.  These can be turned in to giants in Kael (with appropriate faction) for barbed dragonscale boots, frostbringer, cloak of the maelstrom, and barbed dragon scale pauldrons.   Dragons also drop various dragon hide armor of various qualities.  They also drop numerous spells.<br>
<br>
There are over 45 dragons in WW so you can easily have more than one raid at a time in the zone with plenty to kill.  Also there are tons of other mobs that you can pull and kill for xp during downtimes.  I'd recommend scouting the area to find some nice camp spots.  Also research the various dragons for their AEs, levels, etc.  Pulling the wrong dragon can quickly wipe out a raid very easily.  High level Druids and Bards are the best pullers in most cases since mobs like Velium Hounds can out run sow but they can't out run the high speed druid spell (form of hunter I believe) or Selo's.  Rangers and others can pull but from my experience a bard makes the best puller with a druid very close behind. <p><A HREF="http://www.silentredemption.org/" TARGET="_new">
