But anyway... The area marked &quot;safe spot&quot; on the map is ok if you are pulling the harder dragons from the scar (10-17) but for your raid you would rather take the nests (1-9) and the roamers in that area (avoid the Sapara's, Von, and Gargalia for a while, they are alot harder).  You can set up near 4500, -1500 which is just west of #9 but you will get some wanders in that area and there is very little room to move around without agroing things pathing nearby.  I prefer 3700, 3000 (right under the &quot;Western Wastes&quot; on the map).  HUGE area with very few to no wanders.  Gives people some room to move around and not be worried about pushing mobs off the edge into the water or into nearby mobs.  Very nice area.  Easy area to pull dragons 1, 2, 5-9 from.  Go get 3 &amp; 4 if you are moving fast enough.  BTW I'd suggest trying #9 first, Yeldema has no AE and is the easiest dragon there is.  He's the one that shaman can solo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
