<br>
When you are taking people that have never been to WW to hunt dragons 4-5 groups is fine.  I'm sure Clan could do Hate/Fear with 3 groups as well but do you?  Nope.   2-3 solid groups of those knowing what to do and 1-2 more groups of dragon raid newbies so they can learn.<br>
<br>
A 4-5 group raid would be slaughtered by Sontalak and Klandicar in under a minute, Sonta and Klandi are that tough (Von, Cargalia, and the Sapara's would be a rough fight but possible.).  Unresistable AEs will wipe you out fast if you don't have a ton of firepower to drop him quick.<br>
<br>
To give you an idea how tough they are:<br>
<br>
Sontalak: melees for 425 dmg, Flurries, AE pillage (removes 4 buffs),  procs Char (700 DD),  AE DD (up to 650 dmg / debuffs 1 buff)  AE Fear. Unslowable.   He AE's every ~12 seconds (both AEs)   <br>
<br>
Klandicar v2.0: melees for 540+ dmg, Rampages, AE DD (400 dmg LURE based, dispells 1 buff) every 12 seconds, AE Fears, Unslowable. <br>
<br>
Their AE range is huge, approx 300 ft from what I could tell.<br>
